<br>
Now I seem to be getting that Warriors are broken at level 60?  And need something to be a larger percentage better than Hybrids at that point?<br>
<br>
This is all very confusing.<br>
<br>
Let me say my piece.  I learned the hard way that paladins CANNOT **EVER** be given any form of damage reduction (defensive) discipline, because then the high-end game would be trivial.  The high-end game being all about aggro management, not about avoiding damage, you see.<br>
<br>
It was explained to me that having a main tank who could unerringly control aggro would trivialize almost every end-game encounter, because at that point, it's simply a matter of CH cycling and healing the main tank.<br>
<br>
If true, &quot;fixing&quot; taunt for warriors would break the game.  It would be akin to giving paladins a form of defensive discipline.<br>
<br>
From what I'm reading here, warriors are still the acknowledged most efficient main tanks.  More HP, and more AC, than any other class (by how much is subject to debate).  The warrior class has always been one dimensional, much like the cleric class.  So, warriors are the most efficient tanks, Clerics are the most efficient healers and buffers.  All of this comes at a cost.<br>
<br>
Any paladin can tell you that &quot;balance is a range.&quot;  Warriors seem to be moving from near the top of that range (just below monks and rogues) to closer to the bottom of that range.<br>
<br>
I do agree with many ideas stated here, that +hp items should scale by class, or +125hp items should be war only.  I like that idea a lot.  I also like the idea of damage mitigation scaling by armor type, and the idea of a shield allowing a second (or even third check) against the parry skill (monk Block skill simply refers to the parry skill).<br>
<br>
I guess basically as I see it, warriors were at the top end of the balance range for a VERY long time.  They haven't LOST anything, other classes have gained.  That means that warriors have lost ground relative to other classes, but effectively they have remained unchanged.  That makes this whole thing sound like a class envy issue. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=268670" target="new"><img src="http://www.emeraldis.com/~booraembj/smallbah.jpg" align=left> </a> <br> <br> <br><center><font face="coronet, comic sans ms" font size="6" font color="191970"><span style='filter:glow(color=#87ceeb,strength=3);width:100%'> Aragir Lancot</span> </font><BR>
