 a group/raid/guild collaboration.  You don't send everyone in to attack mobs that are going to chew up anyone until the warrior has had some time with the critter.  If the critter after everyone comes in to attack starts turning on other people (people whacking it with weapons), they did something wrong.  If he chews up a wizard, the wizard overnuked.  If he turns on a cleric, the warrior SHOULD be able to help the cleric out by getting it off the cleric (AE Taunt works, level 59 and below, there are problems with this).<br>
<br>
I have not seen significant issues with warriors maintaining agro control on them when the agro control is planned, utilized, and executed.  Taunt has issues for the under 60 crowd, yes, but you can work through it.<br>
<br>
The issue still remains that warriors need to be the best at tanking, and not by a little.  I often use a paladin in an experience group as the primary healer.  The paladin also has great buffs for me, and can root mobs all over the place on a bad pull.  SKs are almost as useful at pulling/splitting as a monk.  AND both pallies and SKs can almost tank as well as I can.<br>
<br>
Defensive?  There are about a handful of mobs that I ever use defensive on anymore.  You don't use defensive in experience groups, or on most big mobs.  You don't need to do it, and if you use it, you just made yourself less flexible to deal with problems that your other disciplines may help you with, or defensive itself if push comes to shove and you need to use it to help a cleric camp.<br>
<br>
I, unfortunately, HAVE read every post on this thread and keep trying to bring up the point that to fix warriors (they aren't broken, just lacking true utility) is to give them a real edge on fighting.  Give us block, or increase parry, riposte, etc.  Give us a different defense chart like monks have their own offense chart.  Give us the ability to truly mitigate damage.  Or maybe give us insane regeneration so that we are harder to kill that way...  A warrior tanking should be a significant (not earthshattering, I am talking about statistical significance) difference in cleric and other healers mana. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20383">Hulanta</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 225<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/7/02 9:20:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=374>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: In reply to Frodlin</span><hr size=1> A valid point Agarir.  Having effective taunt coupled with effective agro weapons would equal surperior agro control.  So it would have to be a give and take.  If taunt is addressed, then the agro from the best weapons would probably have to be reduced.  If taunt is not addressed then the best weapons, or new weapons of similar capability, would need to drop more frequently.  The idea is not to increase the ability of high end warriors to god like with regards to agro control, but to make agro control more realistic for the bulk of the Warriors in the game.  Even out the playing field so to speak.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> In essence, Hybrids have been upgraded by X amount, and warriors have been upgraded by X-1 amount. Many Paladins believe that this has left the classes much more balanced than they were before.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I think everyone will agree that Paladins and Shadow Knights needed a litte catch up work.  And its good that they finally got it.  However, those things that improved the Knights, also improved the Monks, and to a lesser degree the Rangers and the Rogues.  So in essense what we're talking about is all melee have been improved by X, Hybreds have been improved by X+1 (spells have been added and caster changes made in addition to the archetype AAXP melee get) and Warriors have been improved by X-1.  Warriors have lost ground in relation to every melee class, particularly when high end gear is factored into the picture.<br>
<br>
Right now the class is hanging onto its position in the game by the skin of its teeth.  Defensive/evasive is really the only reason to have a Warrior over a Knight as MT, particularly when you add in Paladin LoH and group heals.  500 HP alone just isn't enough, particularly when you're talking the difference between 6500 and 7000 HP.  And additional AC beyond the soft cap it believed to be valueless.  A Monk's greater avoidance can make them viable MTs in the high end game.  If this continues, yes I can see Warriors becoming a raid support class, and not even a very desireable one.  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uchavr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>chavr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/7/02 9:21:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=375>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I'm confused...</span><hr size=1> Actually, the even con or higher thing isn't far off.  Have you ever tried casting on a mob that is white or higher?  You get alot of resists.  Blue mobs are the ones that our spells land on.  <br>
<br>
Consider this if you will.  Until lvl 59 a paladin solo's just slightly better then a warrior.  At 59 we get celestial cleansing which greatly enhances our solo ability.  So for 58 levels of the game we are just as dependant on groups as a warrior.    <br>
<br>
Remember also stun won't have any affect on mobs 55+.  <br>
<br>
Shadowknights probably aren't speaking up as much because they have an ability that they don't have to worry about.  Feign death gives them a slot in a group that warriors can never touch.  Paladins don't have this though.  Our special ability is our diversity.  If warriors are placed back at the top of the tank ladder like they were previously then paladins will get laughed at for groups once again.  Sorry, but I don't want that to happen again.<br>
<br>
Currently we are equal when you add in all the factors.  Saying that &quot;we tank equally&quot; is wrong.  Add in warrior efficiency/hp's/ac/damage/disc's and factoring in paladin spells/utility/taunt means that when all things are added up we can both tank equally.  Using one class over the other presents trade offs.  Depending on what your group needs is depending on which one you want to get.<br>
<br>
Edit here-<br>
<br>
  If warriors are given something to make them the downright best tanks to pick then what slot is left for paladins in an exp group?<br>
<br>
  Why take a paladin when you can get a war/monk/rogue/ranger that can deal more damage?  Why take a paladin when you get a warrior who can tank Y times better?  What slot would we then have?  Our heals are not enough to put us in a exp group.  Who needs paladin heals when a warrior is able to mitigate damage so much better?  Why bother root parking adds when a warrior can ae taunt or a chanter can mez (depends on the level group your in)?  If nothing else a warrior can just go around agroing everything, and with his new improved tanking abilities the group is still better off.<br>
<br>
  Ya'll don't seem to realize that warriors and paladins fill the same basic slot in an exp group.  Sk's fill that spot to a lesser degree.  If warriors are made better ,again, then paladins will be left out in the cold as before.  As it stands currently there is competition for the tank spot in a group.  It's not just a given anymore to take a warrior.  Yeah, it'd be nice to be the only class to fill a certain spot, but that would screw some other class.  Can you honestly say right now that if there is a tank spot in a group a paladin is hands down the best choice?  I know I can't.  I still see warriors get groups when I'm lfg.  I get groups when warriors are lfg.  It's because we are basically on even ground right now.  I pray we never go back to the days that warriors are hands down the best.   <p>Chavr Wyrmbane<br>
60 Crusader<br>
