Druzzil Ro<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvaraho1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 491<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/7/02 10:35:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=378>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I'm confused...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Need a dps/tank? Get a warrior. No one else can do as much damage while taking as much damage. Warriors are still the most efficient melee in the game.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
That would be a monk. <br>
<br>
Ask the priest classes that have had experience who the most mana efficient tank is: not one will say warrior, and that IMO is dead wrong. <br>
<br>
Allot of people say how wrong it is to let warriors have more aggro or knights more defense, but in actuality they just dumped huge amounts of defensive <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> and</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> aggro generation power on the knight classes. <br>
<br>
I will consider this /disc Defensive: I get hit for less damage, you know like the warrior class is suppose to do, sounds good right? Well I also generate less aggro. That's bad. <br>
<br>
Why?<br>
<br>
Because the lower aggro generation powers the MT has, the entire raid has to lower their aggro output by the same amount. End result is just a longer fight, that really could have been made shorter without too much consequence.<br>
<br>
But everyone knows that. Its called Aggro management and everyone has had to do it at some time.<br>
<br>
Now then keeping that in mind envision a class that absorbs damage as well or better than a warrior but then slap more aggro generation on them and figure out who the better tank. <br>
<br>
Now then realize these classes are in the game right now. With the names of Paladin Shadow Knight and Monk.<br>
<br>
So how do you restore balance between these classes without nurfing them to hell and back? Well only one way realy: You would have to give warriors more class based damage absorption power and/or aggro generation power.<br>
<br>
Now then do you see the point? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170513">Varaho Carnicero</a>
