<br>
The problem is, the knights have to be close in tanking ability to warriors or we are just a waist of a group slot. I've seen people saying it on this thread, and knights have know it for a long time, but defense doesn't stack. Either you are good enough to tank, or you aren't. That is the basic problem.<br>
<br>
The fact that this game hes devolved (right from the get go) into encounters of multiple people handling a single target at a time, with one person designated to take all melee damage, is the big problem. That situation doesn't allow melee defense to stack.<br>
<br>
Should warriors be better defensively than paladins and shadow knights? Yes, but by a small margin. I would argue that if AC was fixed so that warriors had an appreciable advantage from higher AC and hp, followed closely by the knights, then a nice gap between the knights and the damage dealing melee, the problem would be solved. None of the damage dealing melee classes have a problem, damage output is one of the major keys to the game, and you can never have too much. (and monks tank just too damn well)<br>
<br>
I'm sure everyone that was in the 50+ game during Kunark and early Velious can remember all the paladins shouting for a group for hours. Can you blame them for being gun shy?  <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686"> Graal MacBladefury</A><BR>
Crusader of Brell<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uclimbatizebladestorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Climbatize Bladestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/7/02 10:56:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=380>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I'm confused</span><hr size=1> &quot;Until lvl 59 a paladin solo's just slightly better then a warrior.&quot;<br>
<br>
ROFLMAO<br>
<br>
Obviously, you've never, ever tried to solo as a warrior.  The only skill warriors *ever* get to help them solo is bind wound (which paladins also have).  By level 15 or 20, down time becomes such a huge problem that a fungi tunic is practically mandatory.  This is why the only warriors you'll ever see soloing are massive twinks.  50k for a fungi, 80k for a CoF, etc.  1% of players can afford what it takes.  Sure, in the end-game warriors can sorta solo, but it is 100% equipment dependent, and highly risky because you need procs to make it work.  And even then, the experience is S-L-O-W.<br>
<br>
Now, let's look at paladins.  You get heals starting at level 9, and these significantly reduce down time (because your HPs regen WHILE you regen mana).  For the princely sum of 400pp you can get unlimited free heals (DW helm) that kick in at level 45.  Then there are spells, Instrument of Nife, root (for parking a double pull), Valor of Marr, etc.  If you stick to undead, not only can pallys solo well, but the Xp can rival that of a good group.  And it's not like finding undead is that hard.  Befallen-Kurn's-Unrest-LGuk-KC Basement.  That's an easy path all the way from 1 to 60.  Sheesh, even the quest for ghoulbane is easy.  I did it in 3 hours (including ports).  IoN + ghoulbane owns undead at level 30.<br>
<br>
This is why it is imperative for warriors to be the best tanks.  There's no plan-B.  The difference has to be clear, not minute as it is today.<br>
<br>
Warriors are broken.  Taunt is a part of the problem, but not all of it.  The fact that the Knights, and monks, have become such good tanks means that an Xp group with a warrior is accutally *inefficient* because the warrior adds no other value.  Something is definitely wrong with the balance.<br>
<br>
Finally: No, I'm not anti-pally.  Actually, I retired my warrior and have been playing a paladin.  I caught on months ago that warriors were broken when I was in LGuk one day.  Every paladin and monk in their 50s can solo there, even with below average equipment.  I was getting owned.  I came to the obvious conclusion - a class with no magic abilities and no special skills doesn't have a place in EQ.  Period.  If warriors didn't have defensive, they'd be extinct already. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=181&stop=200>10</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=907.topic&start=201&stop=220>11</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?t